According to the new timetable of CD (Czech Railways), fewer trains will run for about the same fare.
From 13 December, Czech Railways will terminate or restrict some underutilized express and local trains, while other connections will be strengthened.
The total volume of traffic will be reduced by two percent from the date of validity of the new timetable compared to today.
Most fares including basic and customer fares will not be changed.
For example, the inhabitants of the Ostrava region will have several connections to the capital, and the railway will use Pendolino trains for this route.
The express train will no longer run to Bratislava.
