Two night trains on the Prague - Tabor - České Budějovice route will also be cancelled and the operation of some express trains on the Prague - Pisek - České Budějovice route will be reduced to a few days a week.
One of the biggest changes is the introduction of the new direct route from Milovice to Prague, currently the inhabitants of Milovice have to change trains in Lysa nad Labem.
It is the fifteenth route of the Esko suburban transport system, the opening of which is possible thanks to railway electrification from Lysa nad Labem to Milovice.
Long-distance routes to the capital will end at the destination station Prague - Main Railway Station.
The CD introduces more connecting lines SC Pendolino between Prague and Ostrava and trains to Sumperk/Jesenik will run every two hours.
Since 13 December, passengers can no longer travel to Bratislava with the Pendolino.
This year's bill for regional railways: increase of 200 million
