The experts expect that more than 80 percent of parents will vaccinate their infants against pneumococci from next year.
The vaccination against pneumococci is also groundbreaking in that it is the first area vaccination to be paid for by health insurance companies and not by the state.
The insurance companies should spend the money on prevention, so they save for further treatment, explains Cabrnochova.
Doctors have to buy the vaccines themselves.
