Nearby houses have fetched a purchase price of almost one million pounds (1.1 million euros).
The ground floor includes kitchen, living and dining room, but the Fees Office, a spending control body of the House of Commons, has agreed that Duncan needs more space.
Last year he added a conservatory, which is referred to in the plans as an "orangery".
Neighbors described it as a "glass house for entertainment."
Duncan was also not asked to comment on the increased borrowing during a recent investigation of his previous mortgage contracts by the Committee on Standards and Privileges.
The committee acquitted him of breaking the rules last month after an investigation into his spending.
