And in Stuttgart: a through station, which is located about halfway along the trans-European rail trunk line between Paris and Budapest/Bratislava - hence the slogan of the "heart of Europe".
S21 is now actually being tackled, although the visions of the 80s are no longer compatible with reality.
Even very ambitious planners have recognized that it is almost priceless to implement lowering in the Hessian and Bavarian cities.
However, terminal stations no longer have an entry and exit problem, since there are modern push-pull trains with traction units and control cars at both ends.
